{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f611aa5c-c75a-43f8-9a52-fc3574495327","content":"The directory is empty, so this isn't a repo-specific question. I can answer from general knowledge:\n\n**The problem:** .NET MAUI / Xamarin.Android requires the **Microsoft Build of OpenJDK 17**, not Adoptium Temurin. The Android SDK tooling bundled with .NET expects the Microsoft distribution specifically, and builds can fail with cryptic Java errors when using a third-party JDK.\n\n**Fix:**\n\n1. Install the Microsoft OpenJDK 17:\n   ```bash\n   brew install --cask microsoft-openjdk@17\n   ```\n\n2. Update `JAVA_HOME`:\n   ```bash\n   export JAVA_HOME=\"/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/microsoft-17.jdk/Contents/Home\"\n   ```\n   (Add to your `~/.zshrc` or `~/.bash_profile` to persist.)\n\n3. Verify:\n   ```bash\n   java -version\n   # Should show: OpenJDK ... Microsoft-xxxxx\n   ```\n\n4. Clean and rebuild:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet clean\n   dotnet build -t:Run -f net8.0-android\n   ```\n\n**Why:** The .NET Android workload sets `JavaSdkDirectory` during build. When it detects a non-Microsoft JDK, certain toolchain steps (aapt2, d8, R8) can fail due to subtle version or path differences. The Microsoft build is the only officially supported JDK for .NET MAUI Android development.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a54f9419-6f4e-417a-88a5-0a7a55386fe7","outputTokens":355,"requestId":"D445:298C73:1DABE71:214114F:6A07C211"},"id":"1e2ab828-cd7e-4714-82d4-cb8c35917aa8","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:02:19.131Z","parentId":"1be94ed7-c39c-4cc3-a24b-415a46810cd8"}
